                           <desc>The midpoint of the Psalms in <locus target="#ms_i1">fol. ms_i1</locus> is marked in two ways, with a line of text written entirely in red ink, and with a small harag in the right margin</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                          <locus target="#109v" facs="112">Fol. 109v</locus>
                           <desc>has spaces where text was to have been written in red ink, but was apparently overlooked</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                          <locus target="#7v #8r #11v #14r #14v" facs="010 014 016 017">Fols. 7v, 8r, 11v, 14r, 14v</locus>
                           <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                           </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                          <locus target="#11r #15v #30r #38r #47r" facs="013 018 032 040 049">Fols. 11r, 15v, 30r, 38r, 47r</locus>
